```{r}
  library(usethis)
```

-   usethis package will be helpful for helping us creating our own packages, steps to take:
    -   usethis::create_package("\~/Desktop/") -\> needed Onedrive
    -   Edit DESCRIPTION
    -   make "dev" folder
        -   use_build_ignore
        -   use_git_ignore
    -   use_r to make script
    -   Write Function
        -   what it does
        -   @params
        -   @return
        -   @export
    -   Document Everything: Crtl + Shift + D
    -   Bulid Package: Crtl + Shift + B\
    -   As you work: Crtl + Shift + L
    -   use_package("dplyr")
        -   @import dplyr
    -   OR dplyr:: in package code
-   If you deliberately want a function to be secret, to access reference the package then use three colons (practice:::function)

```{r}
usethis::create_package("~/Onedrive/Desktop/practice")
```

##Unit Test

-   use_test("function")
-   tests -\> testthat -\> test-funname.R
-   ctrl-shift-T

```{r}
test_that("multiplication works", {
  expect_equal(2*2, 4)
})

```
